Azure Blob Storage provides multiple access tiers to optimize cost based on how frequently data is accessed. These tiers help balance storage cost and access performance.

The main tiers are:

* Hot Tier (frequent access)
* Cool Tier (infrequent access)
* Cold Tier (rare access, newer optimization tier)
* Archive Tier (long-term storage, offline access)

For example, frequently accessed application images are stored in the Hot tier, while backups are stored in Cool or Archive tiers.

A real-life use case is an e-commerce platform storing product images in Hot tier and old order logs in Cool or Archive tiers.

Another example is enterprises using Archive tier for compliance data retention.

These tiers help organizations reduce storage costs while maintaining accessibility when needed.
